  "prompt": "Can an overdose of Bisoprolol kill you?",
  "response": "Yes, an overdose of Bisoprolol can be potentially life-threatening. Bisoprolol is a beta-blocker used to treat high blood pressure, heart failure, and other cardiovascular conditions. When taken in excessive amounts, it can lead to severe complications, including:\n\n1. **Severe bradycardia** (extremely slow heart rate)\n2. **Hypotension** (dangerously low blood pressure)\n3. **Cardiac arrest** (heart stops beating)\n4. **Respiratory distress** or failure\n5. **Hypoglycemia** (low blood sugar) in some cases, particularly in people with diabetes\n6. **Loss of consciousness** or coma\n\nIf you suspect a Bisoprolol overdose, seek **immediate medical attention** or call emergency services. Treatment may involve supportive care, such as intravenous fluids, medications to counteract the effects of the overdose, and, in severe cases, interventions like pacemakers or advanced life support.\n\nAlways take the prescribed dose of Bisoprolol and consult your healthcare provider if you have concerns about your medication.",
